text: The Warren G. Harding Presidential Library and Museum is the presidential library of Warren G. Harding, the 29th president of the United States. It was originally set to open on September 4, 2020. However, the opening was postponed because of the COVID-19 pandemic. The library was officially opened to the public May 12, 2021. It is located in Marion, Ohio, close to the Harding Home. ==References== Category:Warren G. Harding Category:Presidential libraries
title: Warren G. Harding Presidential Center
